> tiny is a smaller version, relu uses relu activations in place of mish.

@glenn-jocher The real reason is that yolov4-tiny model introduce a special [[route]](https://github.com/AlexeyAB/darknet/blob/320e6fd8d29f6f7825ef668f15f955f90131f782/cfg/yolov4-tiny.cfg#L49) block, which has new groups and group_id parameters, demonstrated in https://github.com/opencv/opencv/issues/17666#issue-645624234. I've implemented like this:

```python
class RouteGroup(nn.Module):

    def __init__(self, layers, groups, group_id):
        super(RouteGroup, self).__init__()
        self.layers = layers
        self.multi = len(layers) > 1
        self.groups = groups
        self.group_id = group_id

    def forward(self, x, outputs):
        if self.multi:
            outs = []
            for layer in self.layers:
                out = torch.chunk(outputs[layer], self.groups, dim=1)
                outs.append(out[self.group_id])
            return torch.cat(outs, dim=1)
        else:
            out = torch.chunk(outputs[self.layers[0]], self.groups, dim=1)
            return out[self.group_id]

```

